Description: Ostracon, large fragment of the body of a red-grey pottery vessel, the fabric contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (394009) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/394009)
